from an enviromental perspective, forest fires are crucial for certain species to survive. man made influences has created a situation where forest fires are too uncommon that certain species and plants are facing extinction. forest fires also serves the purpose of revitalise the forests and make them more 'healthy'. but as i said, this is from the enviromental point of view. you are indeed correct that uncontralable forest fires are hazardous for humans who live nearby (as well as property). as always, a trade-off must be made.